THE PRIVATE RATED PILOT WAS GIVING A PILOT-RATED PASSENGER A 
DEMONSTRATION FLIGHT IN THE AMATEUR BUILT AIRCRAFT. ACCORDING TO 
WITNESSES, THE AIRCRAFT WAS IN THE TRAFFIC PATTERN ON A TURN FROM BASE 
LEG TO FINAL APPROACH,  WHEN IT DEPARTED CONTROLLED FLIGHT, ENTERED A 
SPIN, AND IMPACTED THE TERRAIN. 
FAILURE OF THE PILOT-IN-COMMAND TO ASSURE THAT ADEQUATE AIRSPEED WAS 
MAINTAINED DURING THE TURN TO FINAL APPROACH, WHICH RESULTED IN AN 
INADVERTENT STALL/SPIN. 
